<font size = 5><b>About Me</b></font><br><br>
I am currently a fifth year Ph. D candidate in mathematics at UPenn (Expected Date of Graduation : May, 2016). My advisor is Richard V. Kadison. I passed my orals in April 2013 with major topic as Analysis (Harmonic Analysis, PDE) 
and minor topic as Riemannian Geometry. You can find the details of my oral exam <a href="http://www.math.upenn.edu/~nsoum/orals.html" class="nounderline">here</a>.
I will be working on problems related to topology and operator algebras for my dissertation.<br><br>
I completed my undergraduate degree in mathematics from the Indian Statistical Institute, Bangalore Centre (B. Math(Hons.) with Distinction) in 2011, during which I spent 3 memorable years
in the city of Bangalore (presently known as Bengaluru). I grew up in the city of Bhubaneswar in Odisha, India.<br><br>
You can have a look at <a href="http://www.math.upenn.edu/~nsoum/res_soum.pdf" class="nounderline">my CV here.</a>
