<font size = 5><b>Odia-\(\TeX\)</b></font><br><br>
Odia (ଓଡ଼ିଆ;  also transliterated as Odiya, Oriya) is one of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Languages_of_India#Classical_languages" class="nounderline">six classical languages of India</a>; the others
being Kannada, Malayalam, Sanskrit, Tamil, Telugu. It is predominantly spoken in the state of Odisha (ଓଡ଼ିଶା).<br><br>

The Odia-\(\TeX\) project is aimed at making \(\TeX\)-based professional typesetting in Odia, easier. Most of the hard work in designing the fonts has been done by Jeroen Hellingman in the <a href="https://www.ctan.org/tex-archive/language/oriya?lang=en" class="nounderline">Oriya-\(\TeX\)</a> project and Anshuman Pandey has added some conjunctive consonants,  written a C preprocessor (Copyright \(\copyright\) 1996-2003, LPPL-GPL License). Here is the <a href="http://ctan.mirrors.hoobly.com/language/oriya/history" class="nounderline">history of contributions</a> to Oriya-\(\TeX\). <br><br>

One may view Odia-\(\TeX\) as a fork of Oriya-\(\TeX\). The main goal is to maintain and systematize the existing work, write elaborate user-friendly tutorials, write a user-friendly preprocessor, add missing conjunctive consonants. The github repository for Odia-\(\TeX\) may be viewed at <a href="https://github.com/nsoum/odia-tex" class="nounderline">https://github.com/nsoum/odia-tex</a>. If you would like to contribute to this project and take it further along with me, feel free to email me to discuss.<br><br>

Excerpt from the short story <b>Rebati</b> by <i>Fakir Mohan Senapati</i> typed using Odia-\(\TeX\) (in Odia Cuttack font, Odia Konark font): <br>
PDF version :  <a href="https://www.math.upenn.edu/~nsoum/odia-tex/sample/rebati-excerpt.pdf" class="nounderline">rebati-excerpt.pdf</a>, 
DVI version : <a href="https://www.math.upenn.edu/~nsoum/odia-tex/sample/rebati-excerpt.dvi" class="nounderline">rebati-excerpt.dvi</a><br>
\(\TeX\) source : <a href="https://www.math.upenn.edu/~nsoum/odia-tex/sample/rebati-excerpt.tex" class="nounderline">rebati-excerpt.tex</a>

